== Potato Wedges ==

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm wide wedges (peeling optional).

Pop the wedges onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Chicken Satay ==

Zest and quarter the @lime{1}.

Chop the @peanuts{20%g}.

Trim the @baby gem{120%g}(half reserved for burger). Keep aside 1 leaf per person. Halve the remaining baby gem lengthways then thinly slice widthways.

Place a hand on top of the @Irish chicken breast{320%g}. Slice horizontally to make two thin steaks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Toss the chicken with the lime zest, half the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet}, salt and pepper.

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

When hot, add the chicken and fry until cooked through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

> TIP: Cook in batches if necessary.

Return the pan to medium-high heat.

Add @coconut milk{1%pack}, @peanut butter{1%sachet}, @Rogan Josh curry paste{1%sachet}, @ketjap manis{1%sachet}, remaining Thai spice, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{1%tbsp}.

> Double sugar and water for 4p.

Stir well to combine and bring to the boil.

Reduce the heat, then cook until thickened and creamy, stirring continuously, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Once reduced, remove from the heat. Add a squeeze of lime juice. Mix together, taste and season with salt and more lime juice if desired.

== Apple Peanut Salad ==

Meanwhile, quarter the @apple{1} and remove the core and seeds. Cut lengthways into thin slices.

Squeeze the remaining lime juice into a #salad bowl{} and mix together with @oil{1%tbsp}.

> Double oil for 4p.

Add the chopped peanuts, apple and sliced baby gem to the bowl with the lime dressing, then toss to coat. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Pop your @brioche buns{2} in the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Assembling ==

Reheat the satay sauce if needed and spread a spoonful over the cut side of each burger bun.

Pop a reserved lettuce leaf on the bun base, top with the chicken, then close with the bun lid.

Serve the chicken burgers with the apple salad and potato wedges alongside.

Pop the remaining satay sauce into a #small bowl{} for dipping.